07/02/2008
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Social Minister Emilia Maslarova told Reuters on Wednesday (February 6th) that Bulgaria plans to import thousands of skilled workers to help implement a number of big international projects in the country.
"We are speaking of tens of thousands of workers, mainly in construction, energy and tourism," Maslarova explained.
Bulgaria is part of both the South Stream gas pipeline project and the Bourgas-Alexandroupolis oil pipeline.
The country is also planning to build a nuclear power plant in the town of Belene, a project worth 4 billion euros.
(Reuters, Mediapool, Actualno - 06/02/08)
